Lines: 353-366

schnorr48_verify_frame() validates dst_addr and payload parameters but does not validate the pubkey parameter before use:

```c
int schnorr48_verify_frame(uint8_t epoch, uint16_t seqnum,
                           const uint8_t *dst_addr, size_t dst_addr_len,
                           const uint8_t *payload, size_t payload_len,
                           const uint8_t *pubkey)  // Not validated!
{
    if (dst_addr_len > SCHNORR48_MAX_ADDR_LEN) {
        return -1;
    }
    if (dst_addr_len > 0 && dst_addr == NULL) {
        return -1;
    }
    if (payload == NULL) {
        return -1;
    }
    // ... pubkey used at line 422 without check
    if (crypto_eddsa_recover_r(R_prime, pubkey, s, e_extended) != 0) {
```

While pubkey is marked _Nonnull in the header declaration, no runtime check exists. If a NULL pubkey is passed:
1. crypto_eddsa_recover_r may crash or return undefined results
2. Subsequent hash operations would process garbage data

Impact: Crash or undefined behavior if caller violates the _Nonnull contract.

Fix: Add explicit NULL check for pubkey, consistent with other parameter validation:
```c
if (pubkey == NULL) {
    return -1;
}
